.TH "kvm_mips_build_exception" 9 "kvm_mips_build_exception" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kvm_mips_build_exception \- Assemble first level guest exception handler.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" kvm_mips_build_exception
.BI "(void *addr "  ","
.BI "void *handler "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "addr" 12
Address to start writing code.
.IP "handler" 12
Address of common handler (within range of \fIaddr\fP).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Assemble exception vector code for guest execution. The generated vector will
branch to the common exception handler generated by \fBkvm_mips_build_exit\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
Next address after end of written function.
